{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:44:02.689Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Common probability distributions"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are mathematical functions that describe how probabilities are assigned to the values of random variables. They are essential for modeling real-world phenomena, performing statistical inference (hypothesis testing, confidence intervals), and building machine learning models in Generative AI. Each distribution has specific parameters (like mean μ and standard deviation σ) that shape its behavior, and different distributions are used for different types of data (discrete vs. continuous) and scenarios."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Common Distributions — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and context"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "probability distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": " defines the probability that a random variable takes on each possible value."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Two main types"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Discrete distributions"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": For countable outcomes (dice rolls, coin flips) → use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Probability Mass Function (PMF)"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Continuous distributions"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": For infinite outcomes (height, temperature) → use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Probability Density Function (PDF)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[medium](https://medium.com/analytics-vidhya/probability-distributions-in-data-science-and-machine-learning-part-2-a907d84d3211)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key discrete distributions"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bernoulli Distribution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Binary outcome (success/failure, yes/no, 1/0)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Single coin flip (heads = 1, tails = 0)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "p"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = probability of success (X = 1)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PMF"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "P(X = 1) = p\nP(X = 0) = 1 - p"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Properties"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": E = p\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(X) = p(1 - p)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ML application"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Logistic regression for binary classification."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Binomial Distribution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of successes in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "n independent Bernoulli trials"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of heads in 10 coin flips."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "n"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = number of trials\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "p"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = probability of success in each trial"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PMF"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "P(X = k) = C(n, k) · p^k · (1-p)^(n-k)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where C(n, k) = n! / (k! · (n-k)!) = number of combinations."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Properties"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": E = n·p\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(X) = n·p·(1-p)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ML application"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Classification outputs, cross-entropy loss."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Poisson Distribution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of events occurring in a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fixed time/space interval"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with constant average rate λ."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of customers arriving per hour; number of emails received per day."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "λ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = average rate (expected number of events)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PMF"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "P(X = k) = (λ^k · e^(-λ)) / k!"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Properties"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": E = λ\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(X) = λ"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ML application"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Modeling stochastic rewards in reinforcement learning."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Approximation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": When n is large and p is small (p < 0.05), Poisson approximates Binomial."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Geometric Distribution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of trials needed for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "first success"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in Bernoulli trials."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": How many coin flips until first heads."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "p"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = probability of success"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PMF"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "P(X = k) = (1-p)^(k-1) · p"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Properties"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": E = 1/p\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(X) = (1-p)/p²"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key continuous distributions"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Normal (Gaussian) Distribution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Most natural phenomena (height, temperature, measurement errors)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Human heights, stock returns, test scores."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "μ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = mean (center)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "σ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = standard deviation (spread)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PDF"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x) = (1 / √(2πσ²)) · e^(-(x-μ)² / (2σ²))"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Properties"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": E = μ\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(X) = σ²\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Shape"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Bell-shaped, symmetric around μ\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "68-95-99.7 Rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": - 68% of data within ±1σ - 95% within ±2σ - 99.7% within ±3σ"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ML applications"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Modeling training residuals in linear regression\n- Naïve Bayes models\n- Generative models (VAEs model data as Gaussian)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Special case"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Standard Normal"}, {"type": "text", "text": " Z Normal(0, 1)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "6. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Student's t-Distribution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Sample mean when population variance is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "unknown"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (small samples)./12:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Testing if a drug works with only 20 patients."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ν"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = degrees of freedom (df = n - 1)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Shape"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Similar to normal but with heavier tails (more uncertainty for small samples)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hypothesis testing"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Used in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t-tests"}, {"type": "text", "text": " when σ is unknown./12:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ML application"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Confidence intervals for model performance with small datasets."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "7. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Exponential Distribution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Time "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "until"}, {"type": "text", "text": " next event occurs (with constant rate λ)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Time until machine fails; time until next customer arrives."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "λ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = rate (events per unit time)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PDF"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x) = λ · e^(-λx) for x ≥ 0"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Properties"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": E = 1/λ\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(X) = 1/λ²\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Memoryless"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": P(X > t + s | X > s) = P(X > t) (past doesn't affect future)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ML application"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Modeling time-to-event in reinforcement learning."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Relationship"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": If X Exponential(λ), then sum of n exponentials Gamma(n, λ)."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "8. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gamma Distribution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Sum of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "n independent exponential random variables"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Total time until 5th customer arrives."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "α"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = shape parameter\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "β"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = rate parameter"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PDF"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x) = (β^α / Γ(α)) · x^(α-1) · e^(-βx) for x > 0"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where Γ(α) = gamma function (generalization of factorial)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ML application"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Bayesian priors, modeling waiting times."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "9. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Beta Distribution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Probability of success in Bernoulli trial (probability itself is random)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Uncertainty about coin's fairness."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "α"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = successes (shape)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "β"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = failures (shape)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PDF"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x) = (1 / B(α, β)) · x^(α-1) · (1-x)^(β-1) for 0 ≤ x ≤ 1"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Properties"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": E = α / (α + β)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(X) = αβ / ((α + β)²(α + β + 1))"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ML application"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Bayesian priors for probabilities; Thompson sampling in reinforcement learning."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "10. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uniform Distribution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": All outcomes equally likely within range [a, b]."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Rolling a fair die; random number generator."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "a"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = minimum\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "b"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = maximum"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PDF"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x) = 1 / (b - a) for a ≤ x ≤ b"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Properties"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": E = (a + b) / 2\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(X) = (b - a)² / 4"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ML application"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Initializing neural network weights randomly."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Distributions for hypothesis testing and confidence intervals"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why specific distributions are needed:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Different hypothesis tests require different distributions based on data characteristics./12:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Distribution used"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "z-test"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard Normal (Z)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Population variance known, large sample (n ≥ 30)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t-test"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Student's t"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Population variance unknown, small sample"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "χ²-test"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Chi-square (χ²)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Testing population variance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "F-test"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "F-distribution"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparing two population variances"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Proportion test"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Normal"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Testing population proportion (large n)/12:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": t-distribution approaches normal as sample size increases (df → ∞)./12:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Confidence_Intervals_and_Hypothesis_Tests/12.03:"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Steps_in_Hypothesis_Testing/12.3.03:"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "Distribution_Needed_for_Hypothesis_Testing)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Generating samples from distributions:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Bernoulli: coin flip\nbernoulli_samples = np.random.binomial(n=1, p=0.5, size=1000)\n\n# Binomial: heads in 10 flips\nbinomial_samples = np.random.binomial(n=10, p=0.5, size=1000)\n\n# Poisson: customers per hour\npoisson_samples = np.random.poisson(lam=5, size=1000)\n\n# Normal: heights\nnormal_samples = np.random.normal(loc=170, scale=10, size=1000)  # μ=170cm, σ=10cm\n\n# Exponential: time until event\nexponential_samples = np.random.exponential(scale=1/0.5, size=1000)  # λ=0.5"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computing probabilities:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from scipy import stats\n\n# Normal distribution\nmu, sigma = 170, 10\nx = 180\n\n# Probability density\npdf_val = stats.norm.pdf(x, mu, sigma)\n\n# Cumulative probability (P(X ≤ 180))\ncdf_val = stats.norm.cdf(x, mu, sigma)  # ≈ 0.84 (84% of people ≤ 180cm)\n\n# t-distribution for confidence intervals\nt_stat = stats.t.ppf(0.975, df=19)  # 95% CI, df=19"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bernoulli"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Binary outcome (success/failure); P(X=1) = p"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Binomial"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Successes in n trials; P(X=k) = C(n,k)·p^k·(1-p)^(n-k)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Poisson"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Events in time/space; P(X=k) = (λ^k·e^(-λ))/k!"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Normal (Gaussian)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Bell-shaped; f(x) = (1/√(2πσ²))·e^(-(x-μ)²/(2σ²))"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Student's t"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Unknown variance, small samples; used in t-tests"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Exponential"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Time until event; f(x) = λ·e^(-λx); memoryless property"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gamma"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Sum of exponentials; modeling waiting times"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Beta"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Probability of success (uncertain); Bayesian priors"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uniform"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": All outcomes equally likely; weight initialization"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hypothesis testing"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": z-test (normal), t-test (t), χ²-test (chi-square), F-test (F)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, probability distributions are fundamental: VAEs model data as Gaussian distributions, logistic regression uses Bernoulli/Binomial for classification, reinforcement learning uses Poisson/Exponential for rewards, and Bayesian methods use Beta/Gamma for priors. Understanding these distributions enables proper statistical inference, confidence interval construction, and hypothesis testing for model evaluation."}]}]}}